The paper discusses the concept of differential privacy, which is a privacy constraint for databases. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
